    <font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="3"><b>New Online Batch Wizard Enhancements are Now Available</b></font>
    <font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2"><br><br>
    LexisNexis&reg; is pleased to announce that we have continued to enhance Accurint&reg; with several new online batch offerings, including the ability to search for deceased information on individuals.&nbsp; The new batch offerings and enhancements have been added to the 'Online Batch Section' and are as follows:
    <ul>
      <li>The <b>Advanced Person Batch*</b> enables users to locate personal identifiable information on subjects including full name, Social Security Number (SSN), date of birth, up to three addresses with phone numbers, and deceased information.&nbsp; This batch functions much of the same manner as the Advanced Person Search to return up to 3 subjects, up to 3 addresses per subject, deceased information on subject, and a phone number for each output address.<br><br></li>
      <li>The <b>Deceased Person Batch*</b> enables users to run a search on a subject by Link ID, name, and/or SSN to determine if and when they passed away as well as verify subject name, SSN, date of birth, and last known address.<br><br></li>
      <li><b>Reverse Phone Append*</b> will be moved from the Main Menu, People section, to the Online Batch Wizard.<br><br></li>
      <li><b>Advanced Sex Offender Solution (ASOS batch)*</b> is a web-based solution that tracks the activity of sex offenders in counties that you may be monitoring -- where they have moved from and to along with best known contact information.&nbsp; Customers will receive a weekly alert informing them if there has been activity regarding the movement of sex offenders, and log on to download the "pivot report" showing "move from" and "move to" information.<br><br></li>
      <li>Users will now have the capability to also search by the LexisNexis Unique Identifier or the Link ID data source for the following batch processes:  People Batch and Phones Plus Batch.</li>
    </ul>
    For more information or questions regarding the new Advanced Person Batch, Deceased Batch, Advanced Sex Offender Solution via batch, or any of the LexisNexis batch solutions found within the Online Batch Menu, please contact your account representative.
